Package io.github.ai4ci.config.execution

Interface DemographicAdjustment.Phenomenological<DIST,NUMERIC>

Type Parameters:
DIST - the type used to represent distribution-like adjustments (for example a function or empirical distribution)
NUMERIC - the type used to represent numeric adjustments (for example a simple scalar or a function that produces a numeric value)
All Known Subinterfaces:
DemographicAdjustment._PartialDemographicAdjustment, PhenomenologicalModel
Enclosing interface:
DemographicAdjustment
public static interface DemographicAdjustment.Phenomenological<DIST,NUMERIC>
Age dependent values in the in-host phenomenological model configuration.

These entries adjust time-scales used by phenomenological in-host models such as incubation and recovery delays.
